      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELEPHANT ROCK (10) scored by 6 metres at Williams over 2277m last start, the second win from his past three runs. Hard to know where he gets from this slightly awkward draw. This looks a sterner test than last time but he is good enough to take this out. HES ROYAL BLUE (7) has been racing well of late. Finished fourth at his latest appearance over 1177m at Pinjarra, beaten 4.5 metres. Gets a soft run on the inside of the second line but may need luck at some point. Meets a similar line up and he can take this out. ISLAND TEE REX (5) was responsible for a better effort last time out when runner-up over 1832m at Albany. Should run a big race. FOLLOW MY STRIDE (4) must be included on the back of some solid recent form, most recently when fourth at Northam over 1780m. One for the exotics players.",
